  I. Adding the meta-containerization layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the meta-containerization layer to your build
=================================================

--- replace with specific instructions for the meta-containerization layer ---

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the meta-containerization layer exists next to the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the meta-containerization layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-poky \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to//meta-containerization \
    "


